                                    title: "Understanding Keyword Metrics",
                                    content: "Before you can find great keywords, you need to understand how to evaluate them. Here are the key metrics:\n\n**Search Volume**\nHow many times per month people search for this term. Higher isn't always better - you need volume YOU can capture.\n\n**Keyword Difficulty (KD)**\nA score (usually 0-100) indicating how hard it is to rank. Based on the strength of currently-ranking pages. Under 30 = easy, 30-70 = medium, 70+ = hard.\n\n**Cost Per Click (CPC)**\nWhat advertisers pay for this keyword. High CPC = high commercial value = people make money from this traffic.\n\n**Search Intent Match**\nDoes the keyword align with content you can create? A health blog can't rank for 'buy Nike shoes.'\n\n**Click Potential**\nSome keywords show featured snippets, maps, or shopping results that steal clicks from organic results. Check if organic results actually GET clicked.",
