                                    content: "The meta description is the snippet below your title in search results. While NOT a direct ranking factor, it massively impacts click-through rate (CTR).\n\n**Meta Description Best Practices:**\n\n**Length:** 150-160 characters\n\n**Must Include:**\n‚Ä¢ Primary keyword (Google bolds matching terms)\n‚Ä¢ Clear value proposition\n‚Ä¢ Call to action\n\n**The AIDA Formula for Meta Descriptions:**\n**A**ttention: Start with something compelling\n**I**nterest: What will they learn/get?\n**D**esire: Why is this the best resource?\n**A**ction: Tell them what to do (Learn, Discover, Get)\n\n**Example:**\n'Struggling with SEO? This step-by-step guide teaches you exactly how to rank #1 on Google - even if you're a complete beginner. Start ranking today!'\n\n**Important:** If you don't write a meta description, Google will auto-generate one from your content. This is rarely optimal - always write your own!",
