                                    content: "Header tags (H1-H6) create a hierarchy for your content. Think of them as an outline that both users and Google can follow.\n\n**The Header Hierarchy:**\n\n**H1 - Page Title (ONE per page)**\n'The Complete Guide to On-Page SEO'\n‚Ä¢ Should include your primary keyword\n‚Ä¢ Only use ONE H1 per page\n\n**H2 - Main Sections**\n'What is On-Page SEO?' | 'Title Tag Optimization' | 'Content Best Practices'\n‚Ä¢ Break content into logical sections\n‚Ä¢ Include keyword variations naturally\n\n**H3 - Subsections**\n'How to Write Title Tags' | 'Common Title Tag Mistakes'\n‚Ä¢ Further break down H2 sections\n‚Ä¢ Great for long-form content\n\n**Real Example Structure:**\n```\nH1: SEO Guide for Beginners\n  H2: What is SEO?\n    H3: How Search Engines Work\n    H3: Why SEO Matters\n  H2: Keyword Research\n    H3: Finding Keywords\n    H3: Keyword Tools\n  H2: On-Page SEO\n```\n\n**Key Rule:** Headers should make sense if you read ONLY the headers - like a table of contents."
