                                    title: "Mobile-First Indexing",
                                    content: "Google now uses the MOBILE version of your site for indexing and ranking - even for desktop searches. If your mobile site is broken, your rankings will suffer.\n\n**What Mobile-First Means:**\n‚Ä¢ Google's crawler acts like a mobile device\n‚Ä¢ Your mobile content is what gets indexed\n‚Ä¢ Mobile usability is a ranking factor\n\n**Mobile Optimization Checklist:**\n\n**Responsive Design**\n‚Ä¢ Site adapts to any screen size\n‚Ä¢ Same URL for mobile and desktop\n‚Ä¢ Content is identical across devices\n\n**Touch-Friendly**\n‚Ä¢ Buttons/links at least 48x48 pixels\n‚Ä¢ Adequate spacing between tap targets\n‚Ä¢ No hover-only functionality\n\n**Readable Without Zooming**\n‚Ä¢ Font size minimum 16px\n‚Ä¢ Content fits screen width\n‚Ä¢ No horizontal scrolling\n\n**Test your mobile experience:** Google's Mobile-Friendly Test tool\n\n**Common Mobile Mistakes:**\n‚Ä¢ Content hidden behind 'Read more' buttons (Google might not see it)\n‚Ä¢ Pop-ups that cover content\n‚Ä¢ Videos that don't play on mobile\n‚Ä¢ Forms that are impossible to fill out",
