                                    title: "XML Sitemaps & Robots.txt",
                                    content: "These two files tell Google what to crawl - and what NOT to crawl.\n\n**XML Sitemap**\nA file that lists all the pages you want Google to index. Like handing Google a map of your site.\n\nLocation: yoursite.com/sitemap.xml\n\n**What to Include:**\n‚Ä¢ All important pages\n‚Ä¢ Last modified dates\n‚Ä¢ Priority hints (optional)\n\n**What NOT to Include:**\n‚Ä¢ Pages you don't want indexed\n‚Ä¢ Duplicate content\n‚Ä¢ Paginated archives\n\n**Robots.txt**\nA file that tells crawlers which pages NOT to access.\n\nLocation: yoursite.com/robots.txt\n\n**Common Uses:**\n```\nUser-agent: *\nDisallow: /admin/\nDisallow: /private/\nAllow: /public/\nSitemap: https://yoursite.com/sitemap.xml\n```\n\n**WARNING:** Robots.txt blocking ‚â† noindex. Blocked pages can still appear in search results if other sites link to them! Use meta robots noindex if you truly want pages out of Google.",
