                                    content: "HTTPS (the padlock icon) is a confirmed Google ranking factor. Sites without it get a 'Not Secure' warning in browsers.\n\n**What HTTPS Does:**\n‚Ä¢ Encrypts data between user and server\n‚Ä¢ Verifies site identity\n‚Ä¢ Builds user trust\n‚Ä¢ Small ranking boost from Google\n\n**Migration Checklist:**\n\n**1. Get an SSL Certificate**\nMost hosts offer free certificates via Let's Encrypt. Premium certificates available for extra validation.\n\n**2. Update Internal Links**\nChange all http:// links to https://\n\n**3. Set Up Redirects**\n301 redirect all HTTP pages to HTTPS versions\n\n**4. Update External Resources**\nImages, scripts, fonts - all must load via HTTPS (mixed content warnings)\n\n**5. Update Google Search Console**\nAdd the HTTPS version as a new property\n\n**6. Update Sitemap**\nAll URLs should be HTTPS\n\n**Common HTTPS Mistakes:**\n‚Ä¢ Mixed content (some resources still HTTP)\n‚Ä¢ Broken redirects\n‚Ä¢ Certificate expiration\n‚Ä¢ Not updating canonical tags",
