                                    type: "concept",
                                    title: "NAP Consistency & Citations",
                                    content: "NAP = Name, Address, Phone Number. Consistency across the web is CRITICAL for local SEO.\n\n**Why NAP Matters:**\nGoogle cross-references your business info across many sources. Inconsistencies create confusion and hurt rankings.\n\n**Example of Inconsistency:**\n‚Ä¢ Google: 'Smith Therapy, 123 Main St, Suite 100'\n‚Ä¢ Yelp: 'Smith Therapy LLC, 123 Main Street #100'\n‚Ä¢ Facebook: 'Dr. Smith Therapy, 123 Main St.'\n\nThese look like different businesses to Google!\n\n**Citations**\nA citation is any online mention of your NAP. They help establish your business's existence and location.\n\n**Key Citation Sources:**\n‚Ä¢ Yelp\n‚Ä¢ Facebook Business\n‚Ä¢ Apple Maps\n‚Ä¢ Bing Places\n‚Ä¢ Yellow Pages\n‚Ä¢ Industry-specific directories\n‚Ä¢ Local Chamber of Commerce\n\n**Citation Best Practices:**\n‚Ä¢ Use IDENTICAL NAP everywhere\n‚Ä¢ Claim and update listings regularly\n‚Ä¢ Remove duplicate listings\n‚Ä¢ Focus on quality sources in your industry\n\n**Tools:** BrightLocal, Moz Local, Yext can help manage citations at scale.",
