                                    content: "Imagine walking into a hospital and hearing: 'The patient presents with acute cholecystitis, requires a laparoscopic cholecystectomy, and has a history of GERD and CHF.' Sounds like a foreign language, right? That's because it IS a language - and you're about to become fluent in it.\n\nMedical terminology is built on a logical system developed over 2,000 years ago, primarily from Greek and Latin roots. The beautiful thing? Once you understand the RULES, you can decode almost ANY medical term - even ones you've never seen before.\n\nThis isn't about memorizing a dictionary. It's about learning a CODE. By the end of this course, you'll look at 'electrocardiogram' and instantly see: electr/o (electricity) + cardi/o (heart) + gram (record) = 'a record of the heart's electrical activity.' Let's crack the code!",
