                                    content: "If the word root is the STAR of the show, the prefix is the DIRECTOR - it tells the root what to do, where to go, or how to behave. Prefixes attach to the BEGINNING of a term and modify its meaning in powerful ways.\n\nConsider this: The root CARDIA means heart. But watch what happens when we add prefixes:\n- TACHY-cardia = FAST heart rate (over 100 bpm)\n- BRADY-cardia = SLOW heart rate (under 60 bpm)\n- ENDO-cardium = INNER lining of the heart\n- PERI-cardium = membrane AROUND the heart\n- MYO-cardium = heart MUSCLE\n\nSame heart, completely different meanings! That's the power of prefixes.\n\nIn this lesson, you'll master the most important medical prefixes - organized into logical groups so they're easy to remember. By the end, you'll be able to instantly recognize what a prefix is telling you about size, location, number, time, or condition.",
