                                    content: "Diagnostic suffixes tell you about TESTS and EXAMINATIONS. These suffixes help you identify whether a term refers to the process of testing, the instrument used, or the result:\n\n**-SCOPY** = Process of VIEWING/examining\n- EndoSCOPY = viewing inside (with a scope)\n- ColonnoSCOPY = viewing the colon\n- ArthroSCOPY = viewing a joint\n- LaparoSCOPY = viewing the abdomen\n\n**-SCOPE** = The INSTRUMENT used for viewing\n- EndoSCOPE = instrument to view inside\n- StetheSCOPE = instrument to listen to chest\n- OthoSCOPE = instrument to view the ear\n\n**-GRAPHY** = Process of RECORDING an image\n- MammoGRAPHY = process of recording breast images\n- RadioGRAPHY = process of recording with x-rays\n- EchocardioGRAPHY = recording heart images with sound\n\n**-GRAM** = The RECORD or image itself\n- MammoGRAM = the breast image\n- ElectrocardioGRAM = the heart electrical record (EKG)\n- EncephaloGRAM = the brain record (EEG)\n\n**MEMORY TIP:** -GRAPHY is the PROCESS (the -ing action), -GRAM is the PRODUCT (the result)!",
